  40. ‌#define COMPARE_POLL_PERIOD 1024

  42. /* Free the compare stack if needed */
  43. ‌static void compare_free_stack(struct compare_stack* stk)
  44. {
  45.   if (stk->stack != stk->init_stack) {
  46.     caml_stat_free(stk->stack);
  47.     stk->stack = NULL;
  48.   }
  49. }

  51. /* Same, then raise Out_of_memory */
  52. CAMLnoreturn_start
  53. static void compare_stack_overflow(struct compare_stack* stk)
  54. CAMLnoreturn_end;

  56. ‌static void compare_stack_overflow(struct compare_stack* stk)
  57. {
  58.   caml_gc_message (0x04, "Stack overflow in structural comparison\n");
  59.   compare_free_stack(stk);
  60.   caml_raise_out_of_memory();
  61. }

  63. /* Grow the compare stack */
  64. ‌static struct compare_item * compare_resize_stack(struct compare_stack* stk,
  65.                                                   struct compare_item * sp)
  66. {
  67.   asize_t newsize;
  68.   asize_t sp_offset = sp - stk->stack;
  69.   struct compare_item * newstack;

  71.   if (stk->stack == stk->init_stack) {
  72.     newsize = COMPARE_STACK_MIN_ALLOC_SIZE;
  73.     newstack = caml_stat_alloc_noexc(sizeof(struct compare_item) * newsize);
  74.     if (newstack == NULL) compare_stack_overflow(stk);
  75.     memcpy(newstack, stk->init_stack,
  76.            sizeof(struct compare_item) * COMPARE_STACK_INIT_SIZE);
  77.   } else {
  78.     newsize = 2 * (stk->limit - stk->stack);
  79.     if (newsize >= COMPARE_STACK_MAX_SIZE) compare_stack_overflow(stk);
  80.     newstack = caml_stat_resize_noexc(stk->stack,
  81.                                       sizeof(struct compare_item) * newsize);
  82.     if (newstack == NULL) compare_stack_overflow(stk);
  83.   }
  84.   stk->stack = newstack;
  85.   stk->limit = newstack + newsize;
  86.   return newstack + sp_offset;
  87. }

  89. static intnat do_compare_val(struct compare_stack* stk,
  90.                              value v1, value v2, int total);

  92. ‌static intnat compare_val(value v1, value v2, int total)
  93. {
  94.   struct compare_stack stk;
  95.   intnat res;
  96.   stk.stack = stk.init_stack;
  97.   stk.limit = stk.stack + COMPARE_STACK_INIT_SIZE;
  98.   res = do_compare_val(&stk, v1, v2, total);
  99.   compare_free_stack(&stk);
  100.   return res;
  101. }

  103. ‌static void run_pending_actions(struct compare_stack* stk,
  104.                                 struct compare_item* sp)
  105. {
  106.   value exn;
  107.   value* roots_start = (value*)(stk->stack);
  108.   size_t roots_length =
  109.     (sp - stk->stack)
  110.     * sizeof(struct compare_item) / sizeof(value);
  111.   Begin_roots_block(roots_start, roots_length);
  112.   exn = caml_do_pending_actions_exn();
  113.   End_roots();
  114.   if (Is_exception_result(exn)) {
  115.     exn = Extract_exception(exn);
  116.     compare_free_stack(stk);
  117.     caml_raise(exn);
  118.   }
  119. }

  121. /* Structural comparison */


  124. ‌#define LESS -1
  125. ‌#define EQUAL 0
  126. ‌#define GREATER 1
  127. ‌#define UNORDERED ((intnat)1 << (8 * sizeof(value) - 1))

  129. /* The return value of compare_val is as follows:
  130.       > 0                 v1 is greater than v2
  131.       0                   v1 is equal to v2
  132.       < 0 and > UNORDERED v1 is less than v2
  133.       UNORDERED           v1 and v2 cannot be compared */

  135. ‌static intnat do_compare_val(struct compare_stack* stk,
  136.                              value v1, value v2, int total)
  137. {
  138.   struct compare_item * sp;
  139.   tag_t t1, t2;
  140.   int poll_timer;

  142.   sp = stk->stack;
  143.   while (1) {
  144.     poll_timer = COMPARE_POLL_PERIOD;
  145.     while (--poll_timer > 0) {
  146.       if (v1 == v2 && total) goto next_item;
  147.       if (Is_long(v1)) {
  148.         if (v1 == v2) goto next_item;
  149.         if (Is_long(v2))
  150.           return Long_val(v1) - Long_val(v2);
  151.         /* Subtraction above cannot overflow and cannot result in UNORDERED */
  152.         switch (Tag_val(v2)) {
  153.           case Forward_tag:
  154.             v2 = Forward_val(v2);
  155.             continue;
  156.           case Custom_tag: {
  157.             int res;
  158.             int (*compare)(value v1, value v2) =
  159.               Custom_ops_val(v2)->compare_ext;
  160.             if (compare == NULL) break;  /* for backward compatibility */
  161.             Caml_state->compare_unordered = 0;
  162.             res = compare(v1, v2);
  163.             if (Caml_state->compare_unordered && !total) return UNORDERED;
  164.             if (res != 0) return res;
  165.             goto next_item;
  166.           }
  167.           default: /*fallthrough*/;
  168.           }

  170.         return LESS;                /* v1 long < v2 block */
  171.       }
  172.       if (Is_long(v2)) {
  173.         switch (Tag_val(v1)) {
  174.           case Forward_tag:
  175.             v1 = Forward_val(v1);
  176.             continue;
  177.           case Custom_tag: {
  178.             int res;
  179.             int (*compare)(value v1, value v2) =
  180.               Custom_ops_val(v1)->compare_ext;
  181.             if (compare == NULL) break;  /* for backward compatibility */
  182.             Caml_state->compare_unordered = 0;
  183.             res = compare(v1, v2);
  184.             if (Caml_state->compare_unordered && !total) return UNORDERED;
  185.             if (res != 0) return res;
  186.             goto next_item;
  187.           }
  188.           default: /*fallthrough*/;
  189.           }
  190.         return GREATER;            /* v1 block > v2 long */
  191.       }
  192.       t1 = Tag_val(v1);
  193.       t2 = Tag_val(v2);
  194.       if (t1 != t2) {
  195.           /* Besides long/block comparisons, the only forms of
  196.              heterogeneous comparisons we support are:
  197.              - Forward_tag pointers, which may point to values of any type, and
  198.              - comparing Infix_tag and Closure_tag functions (#9521).

  200.              Other heterogeneous cases may still happen due to
  201.              existential types, and we just compare the tags.
  202.           */
  203.           if (t1 == Forward_tag) { v1 = Forward_val (v1); continue; }
  204.           if (t2 == Forward_tag) { v2 = Forward_val (v2); continue; }
  205.           if (t1 == Infix_tag) t1 = Closure_tag;
  206.           if (t2 == Infix_tag) t2 = Closure_tag;
  207.           if (t1 != t2)
  208.               return (intnat)t1 - (intnat)t2;
  209.       }
  210.       switch(t1) {
  211.       case Forward_tag: {
  212.           v1 = Forward_val (v1);
  213.           v2 = Forward_val (v2);
  214.           continue;
  215.       }
  216.       case String_tag: {
  217.         mlsize_t len1, len2;
  218.         int res;
  219.         if (v1 == v2) break;
  220.         len1 = caml_string_length(v1);
  221.         len2 = caml_string_length(v2);
  222.         res = memcmp(String_val(v1), String_val(v2),
  223.                      len1 <= len2 ? len1 : len2);
  224.         if (res < 0) return LESS;
  225.         if (res > 0) return GREATER;
  226.         if (len1 != len2) return len1 - len2;
  227.         break;
  228.       }
  229.       case Double_tag: {
  230.         double d1 = Double_val(v1);
  231.         double d2 = Double_val(v2);
  232.         if (d1 < d2) return LESS;
  233.         if (d1 > d2) return GREATER;
  234.         if (d1 != d2) {
  235.           if (! total) return UNORDERED;
  236.           /* One or both of d1 and d2 is NaN.  Order according to the
  237.              convention NaN = NaN and NaN < f for all other floats f. */
  238.           if (d1 == d1) return GREATER; /* d1 is not NaN, d2 is NaN */
  239.           if (d2 == d2) return LESS;    /* d2 is not NaN, d1 is NaN */
  240.           /* d1 and d2 are both NaN, thus equal: continue comparison */
  241.         }
  242.         break;
  243.       }
  244.       case Double_array_tag: {
  245.         mlsize_t sz1 = Wosize_val(v1) / Double_wosize;
  246.         mlsize_t sz2 = Wosize_val(v2) / Double_wosize;
  247.         mlsize_t i;
  248.         if (sz1 != sz2) return sz1 - sz2;
  249.         for (i = 0; i < sz1; i++) {
  250.           double d1 = Double_flat_field(v1, i);
  251.           double d2 = Double_flat_field(v2, i);
  252.           if (d1 < d2) return LESS;
  253.           if (d1 > d2) return GREATER;
  254.           if (d1 != d2) {
  255.             if (! total) return UNORDERED;
  256.             /* See comment for Double_tag case */
  257.             if (d1 == d1) return GREATER;
  258.             if (d2 == d2) return LESS;
  259.           }
  260.         }
  261.         break;
  262.       }
  263.       case Abstract_tag:
  264.         compare_free_stack(stk);
  265.         caml_invalid_argument("compare: abstract value");
  266.       case Closure_tag:
  267.       case Infix_tag:
  268.         compare_free_stack(stk);
  269.         caml_invalid_argument("compare: functional value");
  270.       case Cont_tag:
  271.         compare_free_stack(stk);
  272.         caml_invalid_argument("compare: continuation value");
  273.       case Object_tag: {
  274.         intnat oid1 = Oid_val(v1);
  275.         intnat oid2 = Oid_val(v2);
  276.         if (oid1 != oid2) return oid1 - oid2;
  277.         break;
  278.       }
  279.       case Custom_tag: {
  280.         int res;
  281.         int (*compare)(value v1, value v2) = Custom_ops_val(v1)->compare;
  282.         /* Hardening against comparisons between different types */
  283.         if (compare != Custom_ops_val(v2)->compare) {
  284.           return strcmp(Custom_ops_val(v1)->identifier,
  285.                         Custom_ops_val(v2)->identifier) < 0
  286.                  ? LESS : GREATER;
  287.         }
  288.         if (compare == NULL) {
  289.           compare_free_stack(stk);
  290.           caml_invalid_argument("compare: abstract value");
  291.         }
  292.         Caml_state->compare_unordered = 0;
  293.         res = compare(v1, v2);
  294.         if (Caml_state->compare_unordered && !total) return UNORDERED;
  295.         if (res != 0) return res;
  296.         break;
  297.       }
  298.       default: {
  299.         mlsize_t sz1 = Wosize_val(v1);
  300.         mlsize_t sz2 = Wosize_val(v2);
  301.         /* Compare sizes first for speed */
  302.         if (sz1 != sz2) return sz1 - sz2;
  303.         if (sz1 == 0) break;
  304.         /* Remember that we still have to compare fields 1 ... sz - 1. */
  305.         if (sz1 > 1) {
  306.           if (sp >= stk->limit) sp = compare_resize_stack(stk, sp);
  307.           struct compare_item* next = sp++;
  308.           next->v1 = v1;
  309.           next->v2 = v2;
  310.           next->size = Val_long(sz1);
  311.           next->offset = Val_long(1);
  312.         }
  313.         /* Continue comparison with first field */
  314.         v1 = Field(v1, 0);
  315.         v2 = Field(v2, 0);
  316.         continue;
  317.       }
  318.       }
  319.     next_item:
  320.       /* Pop one more item to compare, if any */
  321.       if (sp == stk->stack) return EQUAL; /* we're done */

  323.       struct compare_item* last = sp-1;
  324.       v1 = Field(last->v1, Long_val(last->offset));
  325.       v2 = Field(last->v2, Long_val(last->offset));
  326.       last->offset += 2;/* Long_val(last->offset) += 1 */
  327.       if (last->offset == last->size) sp--;
  328.     }
  329.     /* Poll for actions */
  330.     if (caml_check_pending_actions()) {
  331.       /* Preserve v1, v2 if a GC occurs.  Registering v1 and v2 directly
  332.          as roots would prevent them from being allocated to registers. */
  333.       value root_v1 = v1, root_v2 = v2;
  334.       Begin_roots2(root_v1, root_v2);
  335.       run_pending_actions(stk, sp);
  336.       v1 = root_v1; v2 = root_v2;
  337.       End_roots();
  338.     }
  339.     /* Resume comparison after resetting poll_timer */
  340.   }
  341. }

  343. ‌CAMLprim value caml_compare(value v1, value v2)
  344. {
  345.   intnat res = compare_val(v1, v2, 1);
  346.   if (res < 0)
  347.     return Val_int(LESS);
  348.   else if (res > 0)
  349.     return Val_int(GREATER);
  350.   else
  351.     return Val_int(EQUAL);
  352. }

  354. ‌CAMLprim value caml_equal(value v1, value v2)

  356.   intnat res = compare_val(v1, v2, 0);
  357.   return Val_int(res == 0);
  358. }
